  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently positioned just below the GEX flip at 6575 in a strong PIN regime with massive positive gamma walls stacked above, creating significant selling pressure on any rally attempt toward the 6580 max gamma strike. The 66.6% 1-minute GEX surge indicates dealers are aggressively hedging by selling futures into strength as we approach these gamma walls, expecting mean reversion back toward the 6550 negative gamma zone where they'll flip to buying dips. \n\nWatch 6575 as the critical pivot—failure to reclaim keeps dealers in sell-mode on rallies, while a sustained break above 6580 could trigger short covering as dealers chase the move higher through the stacked gamma walls at 6585-6590.",
